1
00:01:02,796 --> 00:01:04,697
Narrator:
IN AN OLD HOUSE IN PARIS

2
00:01:04,731 --> 00:01:07,600
THAT WAS COVERED
WITH VINES...

3
00:01:07,867 --> 00:01:08,835
[WOOF WOOF]

4
00:01:08,868 --> 00:01:10,703
[WOOF WOOF]

5
00:01:12,806 --> 00:01:14,774
LIVED 12 LITTLE GIRLS

6
00:01:14,808 --> 00:01:17,110
IN 2 STRAIGHT LINES.

7
00:01:20,346 --> 00:01:21,681
THEY LEFT THE HOUSE

8
00:01:21,714 --> 00:01:23,483
AT HALF PAST 9:00

9
00:01:23,516 --> 00:01:25,285
IN 2 STRAIGHT LINES

10
00:01:25,318 --> 00:01:28,188
IN RAIN OR SHINE.

11
00:01:29,255 --> 00:01:30,924
HEE HEE HEE!

12
00:01:30,957 --> 00:01:35,261
THE SMALLEST ONE
WAS MADELINE.

13
00:01:35,295 --> 00:01:39,666
FRESH SNOW HAD FALLEN
THROUGH THE NIGHT.

14
00:01:40,500 --> 00:01:42,702
ALL OF PARIS
WAS UNDER WHITE.

15
00:01:42,735 --> 00:01:45,405
THE GIRLS WAITED,
SHIVERING, AT THE GATE.

16
00:01:45,438 --> 00:01:48,741
IT WASN'T LIKE MISS CLAVEL
TO BE LATE.

17
00:01:48,775 --> 00:01:49,742
[COUGHS]

18
00:01:49,776 --> 00:01:50,510
AH-CHOO!

19
00:01:50,543 --> 00:01:53,613
NOW WHAT IS
THAT SOUND THEY HEAR?

20
00:01:53,646 --> 00:01:54,814
OHHH!

21
00:01:54,848 --> 00:01:57,784
SOMETHING IS AMISS, I FEAR.

22
00:01:58,751 --> 00:02:03,857
MISS CLAVEL, IT SEEMS,
HAS CAUGHT A COLD.

23
00:02:03,890 --> 00:02:07,594
NOW, LET THIS NARRATIVE...

24
00:02:07,627 --> 00:02:08,261
UNFOLD.

25
00:02:08,294 --> 00:02:10,864
YOU ARE UNWELL,
MISS CLAVEL?

26
00:02:10,897 --> 00:02:12,665
DO NOT WORRY,
LITTLE GIRLS.

27
00:02:12,699 --> 00:02:15,802
I WILL BE BETTER
TOUT DE SUITE.

28
00:02:15,835 --> 00:02:19,205
AH-AH-AH-CHOO!

29
00:02:20,540 --> 00:02:23,476
[WHIMPERS]

30
00:02:24,777 --> 00:02:27,480
ALLO?
 DR. COHN?

31
00:02:27,514 --> 00:02:28,781
C'EST TRAGIQUE!

32
00:02:28,815 --> 00:02:29,582
AN EMERGENCY!

33
00:02:29,616 --> 00:02:32,952
COME AT ONCE,
S'IL VOUS PLAIT.

34
00:02:37,390 --> 00:02:39,759
MERCI, MRS. MURPHY.

35
00:02:40,760 --> 00:02:42,795
BE CAREFUL.

36
00:02:45,999 --> 00:02:48,334
HMM.

37
00:02:48,368 --> 00:02:49,836
MERCI,
 GIRLS.

38
00:02:49,869 --> 00:02:52,805
WHATEVER WOULD I DO
WITHOUT YOU?

39
00:02:52,839 --> 00:02:54,841
OH, THIS IS NOT GOOD.

40
00:02:54,874 --> 00:02:56,643
YOU MUST STAY IN BED.

41
00:02:56,676 --> 00:02:57,844
BUT MY GIRLS...

42
00:02:57,877 --> 00:03:00,346
Dr. Cohn: THEY
WILL LOOK AFTER YOU.

43
00:03:00,380 --> 00:03:02,582
[OUT-OF-TUNE VIOLIN PLAYING]

44
00:03:02,615 --> 00:03:03,850
OHH!

45
00:03:03,883 --> 00:03:04,484
MY HEAD!

46
00:03:04,517 --> 00:03:07,854
IT ALREADY ACHES
SO BADLY!

47
00:03:07,887 --> 00:03:09,622
Narrator: THE DISTURBANCE,
IT SEEMS,

48
00:03:09,656 --> 00:03:10,790
CAME FROM NEXT DOOR

49
00:03:10,823 --> 00:03:13,326
AT THE HOUSE
OF THE SPANISH AMBASSADOR,

50
00:03:13,359 --> 00:03:15,929
WHERE PEPITO WAS,
SO TO SPEAK,

51
00:03:15,962 --> 00:03:17,764
SETTLING A SCORE.

52
00:03:17,797 --> 00:03:20,266
PEPITO!

53
00:03:20,300 --> 00:03:21,834
HUH?

54
00:03:22,502 --> 00:03:24,804
HOLA,
 MADELINE!

55
00:03:24,837 --> 00:03:26,272
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

56
00:03:26,306 --> 00:03:29,809
MAMA INSISTS I LEARN
TO PLAY THE VIOLIN.

57
00:03:29,842 --> 00:03:30,877
PEPITO,

58
00:03:30,910 --> 00:03:32,845
MISS CLAVEL
IS NOT WELL.

59
00:03:32,879 --> 00:03:35,782
YOUR MUSIC IS
HURTING HER HEAD.

60
00:03:35,815 --> 00:03:36,950
OH.

61
00:03:36,983 --> 00:03:38,284
¡PERFECTO!

62
00:03:38,318 --> 00:03:40,420
I WILL TELL MAMA
NO VIOLIN

63
00:03:40,453 --> 00:03:42,889
TILL MISS CLAVEL
IS BETTER.

64
00:03:43,489 --> 00:03:44,724
TILL TOMORROW!

65
00:03:44,757 --> 00:03:45,959
AH-CHOO!

66
00:03:45,992 --> 00:03:48,494
KEEP HER WARM
AND GIVE HER LOVE.

67
00:03:48,528 --> 00:03:50,396
SHE WILL RECOVER
SOON ENOUGH.

68
00:03:50,430 --> 00:03:53,766
Girls:  MERCI, DR. COHN!

69
00:03:54,901 --> 00:03:56,569
THERE. ALL TUCKED IN.

70
00:03:56,603 --> 00:03:59,806
MISS CLAVEL, YOU MAY
PLAY WITH MY MARBLES.

71
00:03:59,839 --> 00:04:01,541
THEY WILL CHEER YOU UP!

72
00:04:01,574 --> 00:04:03,376
THANK YOU,
MA PETITE,

73
00:04:03,409 --> 00:04:04,777
BUT YOU KEEP THEM.

74
00:04:04,811 --> 00:04:06,713
I KNOW
HOW YOU TREASURE THEM.

75
00:04:06,746 --> 00:04:09,315
DO NOT WORRY,
MES ENFANTS.

76
00:04:09,349 --> 00:04:10,617
YOU MAKE ME HAPPY.

77
00:04:10,650 --> 00:04:12,085
TOMORROW, I WILL BE BETTER.

78
00:04:12,118 --> 00:04:15,788
[COUGHS] AND
I WILL TAKE CARE OF YOU.

79
00:04:15,822 --> 00:04:17,390
Narrator: MISS CLAVEL
WENT TO SLEEP

80
00:04:17,423 --> 00:04:18,825
AS THE GIRLS TIPTOED OUT.

81
00:04:18,858 --> 00:04:22,028
SHH! DON'T WAKE HER!
QUIET NOW!

82
00:04:24,697 --> 00:04:26,799
Narrator: BUT THAT EVENING
AT BEDTIME,

83
00:04:26,833 --> 00:04:29,802
THEY STILL HAD SOME DOUBTS.

84
00:04:29,836 --> 00:04:31,104
All, sadly: OHH!

85
00:04:31,137 --> 00:04:33,873
WHAT MORE CAN WE DO
FOR MISS CLAVEL?

86
00:04:33,906 --> 00:04:37,777
PAPA READS BOOKS TO ME
WHEN I AM SICK.

87
00:04:37,810 --> 00:04:39,412
IL ETAIT UNE FOIS.

88
00:04:39,445 --> 00:04:40,313
HEE HEE HEE!

89
00:04:40,346 --> 00:04:44,017
GRANDMAMA MAKES ME
HER SPECIAL ONION SOUP.

90
00:04:48,388 --> 00:04:49,889
OHH, C'EST BON!

91
00:04:49,922 --> 00:04:52,925
MAMA COMES HOME LATE
FROM HER PERFORMANCES,

92
00:04:52,959 --> 00:04:55,728
BUT WE STILL PLAY
WITH MY DOLLS.

93
00:04:55,762 --> 00:04:58,564
[SQUEAKING]

94
00:04:58,598 --> 00:05:01,567
HEE HEE HEE!

95
00:05:01,601 --> 00:05:03,002
OHH, I REMEMBER,

96
00:05:03,036 --> 00:05:05,405
MAMA WOULD LET ME
STAY IN HER BED

97
00:05:05,438 --> 00:05:07,807
AND BRUSH MY HAIR.

98
00:05:08,841 --> 00:05:11,911
SHE LET ME WEAR
THE NECKLACE
PAPA GAVE HER

99
00:05:11,944 --> 00:05:14,614
WHEN THEY FIRST MET.

100
00:05:19,786 --> 00:05:22,388
BUT NOT ANYMORE.

101
00:05:22,422 --> 00:05:23,222
OHH.

102
00:05:23,256 --> 00:05:25,792
AT LEAST YOU STILL
HAVE YOUR FAMILIES.

103
00:05:25,825 --> 00:05:27,760
I HAVE NO ONE NOW.

104
00:05:27,794 --> 00:05:28,428
[CRYING]

105
00:05:28,461 --> 00:05:31,798
PAUVRE
MADELINE!

106
00:05:31,831 --> 00:05:33,666
NO FAMILY!

107
00:05:33,700 --> 00:05:35,501
HOW SAD!

108
00:05:35,535 --> 00:05:38,738
[ALL CRYING]

109
00:05:42,075 --> 00:05:44,811
SOMETHING IS NOT RIGHT!

110
00:05:45,211 --> 00:05:47,714
SOMETHING IS QUITE WRONG!

111
00:05:48,614 --> 00:05:49,949
[GIRLS CRYING]

112
00:05:49,982 --> 00:05:51,617
LITTLE GIRLS,

113
00:05:51,651 --> 00:05:52,852
WHAT IS WRONG?!

114
00:05:52,885 --> 00:05:56,422
WE ARE SORRY,
MISS CLAVEL.

115
00:05:56,456 --> 00:05:57,757
WE ARE FEELING SAD

116
00:05:57,790 --> 00:05:58,725
BECAUSE--[SNIFFLES]--

117
00:05:58,758 --> 00:06:01,561
POOR MADELINE
HAS NO FAMILY!

118
00:06:01,594 --> 00:06:03,930
Miss Clavel:
MES ENFANTS, 
DO NOT FORGET.

119
00:06:03,963 --> 00:06:07,033
WE ARE NOT ONLY BORN
INTO FAMILIES,

120
00:06:07,066 --> 00:06:09,102
WE CAN ALSO FIND THEM,

121
00:06:09,135 --> 00:06:12,505
JUST AS WE HAVE FOUND
EACH OTHER.

122
00:06:12,538 --> 00:06:15,742
FAMILIES COME IN
ALL SHAPES AND SIZES.

123
00:06:15,775 --> 00:06:17,877
IS IT THE SAME,
MISS CLAVEL?

124
00:06:17,910 --> 00:06:19,512
I DO NOT THINK SO.

125
00:06:19,545 --> 00:06:22,782
WHAT DO WE SAY
AT EACH MEAL?

126
00:06:22,815 --> 00:06:24,917
WE LOVE OUR BREAD,

127
00:06:24,951 --> 00:06:27,186
Girls: WE LOVE OUR BUTTER,

128
00:06:27,220 --> 00:06:29,055
BUT MOST OF ALL,

129
00:06:29,088 --> 00:06:31,524
WE LOVE EACH OTHER.

130
00:06:31,557 --> 00:06:33,025
PERHAPS IT IS SO.

131
00:06:33,059 --> 00:06:35,461
I KNOW
 IT IS!

132
00:06:35,495 --> 00:06:36,896
BUT, MISS CLAVEL,

133
00:06:36,929 --> 00:06:37,997
YOU MUST GO BACK TO BED.

134
00:06:38,030 --> 00:06:39,732
YOU WILL GET MORE SICK.

135
00:06:39,766 --> 00:06:41,000
AND THEN
WHERE WILL WE BE?

136
00:06:41,033 --> 00:06:44,070
All: OH, PLEASE, MISS CLAVEL!
YOU MUST STAY WARM!

137
00:06:44,103 --> 00:06:45,538
GO BACK TO BED,
MISS CLAVEL!

138
00:06:45,571 --> 00:06:46,272
I WILL GO TO BED

139
00:06:46,305 --> 00:06:49,142
IF YOU
 WILL GO TO BED.

140
00:06:54,046 --> 00:06:55,915
[ALL YAWN]

141
00:06:55,948 --> 00:06:58,251
I WILL GO TO SLEEP...

142
00:06:58,284 --> 00:07:02,054
IF YOU
 WILL GO TO SLEEP.

143
00:07:06,259 --> 00:07:07,927
WILL YOU HAVE SWEET DREAMS

144
00:07:07,960 --> 00:07:09,729
IF WE HAVE SWEET DREAMS?

145
00:07:09,762 --> 00:07:12,698
OUI, MA CHERIE.

146
00:07:19,672 --> 00:07:21,641
Narrator:
THE MORNING ARRIVED

147
00:07:21,674 --> 00:07:23,042
AND THE POSTMAN AS WELL...

148
00:07:23,075 --> 00:07:23,910
[DING DING DING]

149
00:07:23,943 --> 00:07:25,645
WITH A LETTER ADDRESSED,

150
00:07:25,678 --> 00:07:27,914
"CARE OF MISS CLAVEL."

151
00:07:27,947 --> 00:07:30,082
[WOOF WOOF]

152
00:07:31,584 --> 00:07:33,519
BONJOUR,
 MISS CLAVEL.

153
00:07:33,553 --> 00:07:34,453
HOW ARE YOU FEELING?

154
00:07:34,487 --> 00:07:38,224
MUCH BETTER,
MA PETITE. 
MERCI.

155
00:07:44,163 --> 00:07:46,866
BON,
 GENEVIEVE!

156
00:07:48,835 --> 00:07:49,936
OOH, LA LA!

157
00:07:49,969 --> 00:07:51,204
AN ANNOUNCEMENT?

158
00:07:51,237 --> 00:07:52,805
AN INVITATION?

159
00:07:52,839 --> 00:07:53,973
A BIRTHDAY CARD?

160
00:07:54,006 --> 00:07:55,842
All: FOR WHOM?

161
00:07:55,875 --> 00:07:56,809
MADELINE.

162
00:07:56,843 --> 00:07:58,778
OUI,
 MISS CLAVEL?

163
00:08:01,914 --> 00:08:03,616
"MIT
 LOVE,

164
00:08:03,649 --> 00:08:07,019
FROM YOUR LONG-LOST
UNCLE HORST."

165
00:08:07,053 --> 00:08:08,955
I AM PART OF A FAMILY!

166
00:08:08,988 --> 00:08:10,857
I HAVE AN UNCLE!

167
00:08:10,890 --> 00:08:12,124
FROM VIENNA!

168
00:08:12,158 --> 00:08:14,260
AND HE IS COMING HERE!

169
00:08:14,293 --> 00:08:15,127
TO SEE ME!

170
00:08:15,161 --> 00:08:17,763
All:
C'EST MERVEILLEUX!
HOW WONDERFUL!

171
00:08:17,797 --> 00:08:19,732
Miss Clavel:
GIRLS, GIRLS!

172
00:08:19,765 --> 00:08:21,033
WE MUST PREPARE!

173
00:08:21,067 --> 00:08:22,568
EVERYTHING
MUST BE READY

174
00:08:22,602 --> 00:08:24,770
FOR MADELINE'S
UNCLE HORST!

175
00:08:24,804 --> 00:08:27,306
HE IS HER FAMILY!

176
