508
00:20:47,779 --> 00:20:50,482
♪ WELL-READ

509
00:20:50,849 --> 00:20:52,484
OUI,
 OUI!

510
00:20:52,517 --> 00:20:55,487
[CLAPPING]

511
00:20:56,655 --> 00:20:57,956
THAT WAS, UH,

512
00:20:57,990 --> 00:21:00,525
MOST ENTERTAINING
FOR MUSIC LOVERS.

513
00:21:00,559 --> 00:21:02,628
DO NOT WORRY,
LIEBCHEN.

514
00:21:02,661 --> 00:21:04,863
YOU WILL ATTEND
MANY CONCERTS IN VIENNA,

515
00:21:04,896 --> 00:21:07,599
JUST AS YOUR
MUTTER 
LOVED TO DO.

516
00:21:07,633 --> 00:21:08,433
NOW, TOMORROW,

517
00:21:08,467 --> 00:21:09,234
WE HAVE AN EARLY START.

518
00:21:09,267 --> 00:21:12,004
THE ORIENT EXPRESS
WAITS FOR NO ONE.

519
00:21:12,037 --> 00:21:12,738
BE ON TIME.

520
00:21:12,771 --> 00:21:14,706
MAIS
 OUI, UNCLE HORST.

521
00:21:14,740 --> 00:21:17,409
ALLOW ME TO DRIVE YOU.

522
00:21:17,442 --> 00:21:18,010
OF COURSE.

523
00:21:18,043 --> 00:21:20,779
OH, YES!
OF COURSE.

524
00:21:20,812 --> 00:21:24,583
I, FOR ONE,
WILL CERTAINLY MISS
OUR MADELINE.

525
00:21:24,616 --> 00:21:25,283
JA.

526
00:21:25,317 --> 00:21:27,986
THERE ISN'T
ANY CHANCE, UH...

527
00:21:28,020 --> 00:21:28,820
NEIN.

528
00:21:28,854 --> 00:21:30,455
THERE IS, UH, OF COURSE,

529
00:21:30,489 --> 00:21:32,891
THE MATTER
OF HER INHERITANCE.

530
00:21:32,924 --> 00:21:34,826
O-OH. HMM.

531
00:21:34,860 --> 00:21:35,861
OF COURSE.

532
00:21:35,894 --> 00:21:36,862
QUITE SUBSTANTIAL.

533
00:21:36,895 --> 00:21:40,132
JA.
 AS HER GUARDIAN,
 I AM RESPONSIBLE.

534
00:21:40,165 --> 00:21:41,366
QUITE, QUITE.

535
00:21:41,400 --> 00:21:43,068
I HAD NO DOUBTS.

536
00:21:47,906 --> 00:21:50,942
Narrator: UNCLE HORST
HAS POLISH, GRACE, AND WIT.

537
00:21:50,976 --> 00:21:53,445
THAT SEEMS
TO BE THE SUM OF IT.

538
00:21:53,478 --> 00:21:57,115
BUT IS THERE MORE
 THAN MEETS THE EYE

539
00:21:57,149 --> 00:22:01,486
TO BE UNCOVERED
BY AND BY?

540
00:22:06,792 --> 00:22:08,527
SLEEP WELL,
MES CHERIES.

541
00:22:08,560 --> 00:22:10,762
Girls: 
OUI,
 MISS CLAVEL.

542
00:22:10,796 --> 00:22:12,831
WE WILL TRY.

543
00:22:12,864 --> 00:22:15,534
OHH!

544
00:22:15,834 --> 00:22:19,438
I CAN'T BELIEVE
THIS IS MY LAST NIGHT.

545
00:22:19,471 --> 00:22:21,039
C'EST HORRIBLE!

546
00:22:21,073 --> 00:22:21,740
NON, NON.

547
00:22:21,773 --> 00:22:24,910
IT IS WONDERFUL
FOR MADELINE.

548
00:22:24,943 --> 00:22:26,545
[CRIES]

549
00:22:26,578 --> 00:22:27,646
OH, MADELINE.

550
00:22:27,679 --> 00:22:29,915
WHAT EVER WILL
WE DO WITHOUT YOU?

551
00:22:29,948 --> 00:22:31,750
DO NOT WORRY,
MES AMIES.

552
00:22:31,783 --> 00:22:33,618
I WILL COME AND VISIT.

553
00:22:33,652 --> 00:22:34,720
PROMISE?

554
00:22:34,753 --> 00:22:35,620
SOON?

555
00:22:35,654 --> 00:22:37,856
SOON AS I CAN.

556
00:22:41,026 --> 00:22:43,829
All: FRIENDS...

557
00:22:43,862 --> 00:22:45,697
FOR NOW

558
00:22:45,731 --> 00:22:48,800
AND FOREVER!

559
00:22:50,469 --> 00:22:51,903
Narrator: WHILE OTHERS
WERE SLEEPING,

560
00:22:51,937 --> 00:22:53,972
ALL WRAPPED
IN THEIR DREAMS...

561
00:22:54,005 --> 00:22:56,842
[RINGS]

562
00:22:56,875 --> 00:22:58,443
THE MUCHACHO
 NEXT DOOR

563
00:22:58,477 --> 00:23:01,079
WAS HATCHING A SCHEME.

564
00:23:14,559 --> 00:23:16,862
[SNORING]

565
00:23:18,563 --> 00:23:19,865
[GATE OPENS]

566
00:23:19,898 --> 00:23:21,733
SQUAW--

567
00:23:21,767 --> 00:23:23,802
SHH.
POR FAVOR!

568
00:23:23,835 --> 00:23:24,770
IF YOU WAKE THE SUN,

569
00:23:24,803 --> 00:23:25,737
THE DAY WILL BEGIN,

570
00:23:25,771 --> 00:23:29,508
AND MADELINE
WILL BE GONE!

571
00:23:30,609 --> 00:23:33,645
A FULL BEAK WILL
KEEP YOU QUIET.

572
00:23:36,014 --> 00:23:38,183
EAT SLOWLY!

573
00:23:38,216 --> 00:23:40,185
CHEW!

574
00:23:42,888 --> 00:23:43,822
AY YAY YAY!

575
00:23:43,855 --> 00:23:44,923
SQUAW--

576
00:23:44,956 --> 00:23:46,758
¡SILENCIO!

577
00:23:46,792 --> 00:23:48,760
DON'T WAKE THE SUN!

578
00:23:48,794 --> 00:23:51,797
GO BACK TO SLEEP!

579
00:23:52,197 --> 00:23:53,698
HMM.

580
00:23:53,732 --> 00:23:55,667
SQUAW--

581
00:23:56,768 --> 00:23:58,904
SHUSH!

582
00:24:00,038 --> 00:24:01,273
[GASPS]

583
00:24:01,306 --> 00:24:04,776
COCK-A-DOODLE-DOO!

584
00:24:05,977 --> 00:24:07,879
Narrator: TRY AS HE MIGHT

585
00:24:07,913 --> 00:24:09,181
TO STOP DAYLIGHT
FROM BREAKING,

586
00:24:09,214 --> 00:24:14,753
PEPITO HAD FAILED,
AND ALL PARIS WAS WAKING.

587
00:24:15,787 --> 00:24:20,492
AND 12 LITTLE GIRLS MET
THE MORNING WITH DREAD...

588
00:24:22,861 --> 00:24:27,032
THINKING OF SORROWFUL
GOOD-BYES AHEAD.

589
00:24:36,241 --> 00:24:37,809
AS THE GIRLS
MADE THEIR BEDS,

590
00:24:37,843 --> 00:24:42,113
IT WAS HARD TO IGNORE
THAT MADELINE, SADLY,

591
00:24:42,147 --> 00:24:45,083
WOULD SLEEP THERE NO MORE.

592
00:24:48,920 --> 00:24:52,057
AND AT BREAKFAST, THE MOOD
WENT FROM GLOOMY TO WORSE

593
00:24:52,090 --> 00:24:55,961
AS THE GIRLS ALL RECITED
THEIR FAVORITE VERSE.

594
00:24:55,994 --> 00:24:58,129
Girls: WE LOVE OUR BREAD,

595
00:24:58,163 --> 00:25:00,932
WE LOVE OUR BUTTER,

596
00:25:00,966 --> 00:25:02,868
BUT MOST OF ALL

597
00:25:02,901 --> 00:25:08,573
WE LOVE MADELINE!
[CRYING]

598
00:25:08,607 --> 00:25:09,507
LITTLE GIRLS,

599
00:25:09,541 --> 00:25:13,945
YOUR TEARS WILL MAKE
THE HOT CHOCOLATE SALTY.

600
00:25:16,348 --> 00:25:20,685
Narrator:
AS TIME GREW SHORT,
THERE WAS PACKING TO DO

601
00:25:20,719 --> 00:25:25,290
WITH MADELINE'S CLOTHES
AND SOME MEMORIES, TOO.

602
00:25:25,323 --> 00:25:26,791
[KISS KISS]

603
00:25:26,825 --> 00:25:28,860
GO WITH MADELINE.

604
00:25:29,294 --> 00:25:31,663
[SQUEAKS]

605
00:25:31,696 --> 00:25:35,901
Narrator:
THE SUITCASE CLOSED,
BUT DID NOT CLICK...

606
00:25:35,934 --> 00:25:38,103
UNH! UNH!

607
00:25:38,136 --> 00:25:42,007
TILL 3 MORE BOTTOMS
DID THE TRICK.

608
00:25:42,807 --> 00:25:44,876
Pepito: AH!

609
00:25:44,910 --> 00:25:47,178
PEPITO WAS SEARCHING
AND HOPED TO FIND

610
00:25:47,212 --> 00:25:49,381
A FAREWELL GIFT
FOR MADELINE.

611
00:25:49,414 --> 00:25:52,083
WHAT WOULD SHE LIKE BEST?

612
00:25:52,117 --> 00:25:54,286
MY SLINGSHOT?

613
00:25:56,054 --> 00:25:58,189
MMM, MAYBE NOT.

614
00:26:00,191 --> 00:26:01,026
AH, MY TOP!

615
00:26:01,059 --> 00:26:04,129
BUT WHERE IS THE STRING?

616
00:26:06,831 --> 00:26:08,300
MY PRIZE TOAD.

617
00:26:08,333 --> 00:26:10,702
SUN-DRIED, OF COURSE.

618
00:26:10,735 --> 00:26:12,070
MMM.

619
00:26:12,103 --> 00:26:14,005
¡SÍ, SI!
 THE BEST OF ALL!

620
00:26:14,039 --> 00:26:16,675
A PRESENT FROM
THE AMBASSADOR OF BRAZIL.

621
00:26:16,708 --> 00:26:20,111
A GENUINE IMITATION
SHRUNKEN HEAD.

622
00:26:21,980 --> 00:26:23,415
[REOW]

623
00:26:23,448 --> 00:26:24,549
¡PERFECTO!

624
00:26:24,582 --> 00:26:27,252
Narrator:
WHILE PEPITO WAS BUSILY
WRAPPING HIS TREAT,

625
00:26:27,285 --> 00:26:31,222
A TAXICAB WAITED OUTSIDE
IN THE STREET...

626
00:26:33,858 --> 00:26:36,161
AS UNCLE HORST
GESTURED AND SAID...

627
00:26:36,194 --> 00:26:37,295
NOW, MY SWEET.

628
00:26:37,329 --> 00:26:38,129
[RAR RAR ARF ARF]

629
00:26:38,163 --> 00:26:42,267
GENEVIEVE RAN
AND JUMPED UP ON A SEAT.

630
00:26:42,300 --> 00:26:43,802
[ARR ARR RAR]

631
00:26:43,835 --> 00:26:44,836
NEIN, NEIN, NEIN.

632
00:26:44,869 --> 00:26:47,439
GENEVIEVE WANTS
TO GO WITH MADELINE.

633
00:26:47,472 --> 00:26:48,773
WE'VE ALL AGREED.

634
00:26:48,807 --> 00:26:49,808
Girls:
OUI, OUI.

635
00:26:49,841 --> 00:26:52,310
SHE WILL KEEP
YOU COMPANY.

636
00:26:52,344 --> 00:26:53,778
UHH!

637
00:26:53,812 --> 00:26:54,946
MERCI, MES AMIES.

638
00:26:54,980 --> 00:26:58,817
THERE ARE NO DOGS
IN THE SCHOOL IN VIENNA.

639
00:26:58,850 --> 00:27:00,118
All: OHH.

640
00:27:00,151 --> 00:27:01,886
THEN THERE
IS NO MADELINE

641
00:27:01,920 --> 00:27:03,989
IN THE SCHOOL
IN VIENNA.

642
00:27:04,022 --> 00:27:04,990
[ALL GASP]

643
00:27:05,023 --> 00:27:07,425
[SIGHS]
JA.

644
00:27:07,459 --> 00:27:09,761
[WOOF WOOF]

645
00:27:09,794 --> 00:27:10,595
Girls: AHH.

646
00:27:10,629 --> 00:27:13,965
AHEM!
I HAVE SOMETHING
FOR THE TRIP.

647
00:27:13,999 --> 00:27:17,135
ALL MADELINE'S NEEDS
ARE PROVIDED FOR,

648
00:27:17,168 --> 00:27:20,939
BUT ANY SPENDING MONEY
MAY BE ENTRUSTED TO ME

649
00:27:20,972 --> 00:27:22,007
FOR SAFEKEEPING.

650
00:27:22,040 --> 00:27:24,175
THIS IS FOR MADELINE.

651
00:27:24,209 --> 00:27:25,276
IS IT VALUABLE?

652
00:27:25,310 --> 00:27:26,711
PRICELESS.

653
00:27:26,745 --> 00:27:30,815
MADELINE,
CLOSE YOUR EYES.

654
00:27:31,783 --> 00:27:33,952
NOW OPEN...

655
00:27:33,985 --> 00:27:35,086
OHH.

656
00:27:35,120 --> 00:27:36,788
MAMA'S BEADS.

657
00:27:36,821 --> 00:27:38,923
I WAS TOLD TO PUT THESE
IN SAFEKEEPING

658
00:27:38,957 --> 00:27:41,826
UNTIL IT WAS TIME
TO GIVE THEM TO YOU.

659
00:27:41,860 --> 00:27:43,294
NOW IS THAT TIME.

660
00:27:43,328 --> 00:27:46,965
I THOUGHT PERHAPS,
UH, DIAMONDS?

661
00:27:46,998 --> 00:27:49,868
EMERALDS? PEARLS?

662
00:27:49,901 --> 00:27:51,436
UHH.
VELL, NO MATTER.

663
00:27:51,469 --> 00:27:55,807
BEADS CAN BE ENTRUSTED
TO A LITTLE GIRL.

664
00:27:55,840 --> 00:27:57,876
MERCI,
 MISS CLAVEL.

665
00:27:57,909 --> 00:27:58,710
AHEM.

666
00:27:58,743 --> 00:27:59,878
JA,
 VELL,
 YOU HAVE ME NOW,

667
00:27:59,911 --> 00:28:01,946
UND
 IT IS TIME
 TO GO.

668
00:28:01,980 --> 00:28:03,281
VE MUST BE PUNCTUAL.

669
00:28:03,314 --> 00:28:05,116
AUF WIEDERSEHEN!

670
00:28:05,150 --> 00:28:07,419
Girls: OHH.

671
00:28:09,087 --> 00:28:12,490
Girls: GOOD-BYE, MADELINE.
WE'LL MISS YOU.

672
00:28:12,524 --> 00:28:14,993
Girl: WE LOVE YOU,
 MADELINE!

673
00:28:15,026 --> 00:28:17,028
[WHIMPERS]

674
00:28:17,062 --> 00:28:19,764
Girls: GONE FOREVER!

675
00:28:19,798 --> 00:28:20,965
[ALL CRY]

676
00:28:20,999 --> 00:28:23,802
LITTLE GIRLS,
DO NOT CRY.

677
00:28:23,835 --> 00:28:26,304
[SNIFFLES]
WE MUST BE HAPPY.

678
00:28:26,337 --> 00:28:27,906
All: HAPPY?

679
00:28:27,939 --> 00:28:29,074
FOR MADELINE.

680
00:28:29,107 --> 00:28:31,810
SHE IS WITH
HER UNCLE HORST,

681
00:28:31,843 --> 00:28:33,144
AND HE IS FAMILY.

682
00:28:33,178 --> 00:28:38,116
WE CAN WRITE,
AND ONE DAY
PERHAPS EVEN VISIT!

683
00:28:38,149 --> 00:28:39,084
WHEN?

684
00:28:39,117 --> 00:28:41,286
PAUVRES PETITES.

685
00:28:41,319 --> 00:28:43,421
[WHIMPERS]

686
00:28:46,991 --> 00:28:48,059
Pepito: WAIT!

687
00:28:48,093 --> 00:28:51,229
AM I TOO LATE?
WHERE IS MADELINE?

688
00:28:51,262 --> 00:28:52,864
SHE IS GONE.

689
00:28:52,897 --> 00:28:56,301
Girls: FOREVER!

690
00:28:57,302 --> 00:28:58,470
NOOO!

691
00:28:58,503 --> 00:29:02,474
Narrator:
THE AMBASSADOR'S CAR,
WITH THE GIRLS AND PEPITO,

692
00:29:02,507 --> 00:29:05,009
SPED OFF TO THE TAXI
AS HE YELLED...

693
00:29:05,043 --> 00:29:08,880
¡RAPIDO!
 FASTER!

694
00:29:09,547 --> 00:29:11,416
WHILE THE TRAIN DEPOT
WAS JUST AHEAD,

695
00:29:11,449 --> 00:29:15,019
THE TAXI CAB STOPPED
AT THE METRO INSTEAD.

696
00:29:15,053 --> 00:29:16,154
UNCLE.

697
00:29:16,187 --> 00:29:17,288
UNCLE?

698
00:29:17,322 --> 00:29:19,424
HMM?
JA, LIEBCHEN?

699
00:29:19,457 --> 00:29:20,825
WHY DO WE STOP HERE?

700
00:29:20,859 --> 00:29:23,561
THIS IS NOT
THE TRAIN STATION.

701
00:29:23,595 --> 00:29:24,362
BECAUSE, UH,

702
00:29:24,395 --> 00:29:26,898
BEFORE THE TRAIN,
VE NEED TO GO TO,

703
00:29:26,931 --> 00:29:28,867
UH, THE...BOUTIQUE.

704
00:29:28,900 --> 00:29:31,202
LA BOUTIQUE? POURQUOI?

705
00:29:31,236 --> 00:29:34,305
WHY? FOR...A DRESS.

706
00:29:34,339 --> 00:29:36,908
UND
 VAT A DRESS.

707
00:29:36,941 --> 00:29:38,943
A FORMAL
PRESENTATION DRESS.

708
00:29:38,977 --> 00:29:40,612
MIT,
 UM, UM,

709
00:29:40,645 --> 00:29:43,181
SPARKLY THINGS
ALL DOWN THE FRONT.

710
00:29:43,214 --> 00:29:44,182
COME!

711
00:29:44,215 --> 00:29:45,884
BUT...

712
00:29:50,321 --> 00:29:51,222
PEPITO.

713
00:29:51,256 --> 00:29:53,825
WHAT IS IN
YOUR PACKAGE?

714
00:29:57,061 --> 00:29:59,564
[ALL GASP]

715
00:29:59,597 --> 00:30:02,300
[TIRES SCREECH]

716
00:30:06,037 --> 00:30:08,139
PUT IT AWAY!

717
00:30:13,478 --> 00:30:17,882
Narrator: DOWN IN
THE METRO, TRAINS COME,
THEN THEY LEAVE.

718
00:30:19,083 --> 00:30:21,119
EVERYONE WAS ON BOARD...

719
00:30:21,152 --> 00:30:23,021
[WOOF WOOF]

720
00:30:23,054 --> 00:30:25,056
EXCEPT GENEVIEVE.

721
00:30:25,089 --> 00:30:26,624
GENEVIEVE!

722
00:30:26,658 --> 00:30:28,660
NO DOGS ALLOWED
ON THE METRO.

723
00:30:28,693 --> 00:30:30,929
SHE VILL VAIT
UNTIL VE GET BACK.

724
00:30:30,962 --> 00:30:31,930
NON!

725
00:30:31,963 --> 00:30:32,964
JA.

726
00:30:32,997 --> 00:30:34,632
GENEVIEVE!

727
00:30:34,666 --> 00:30:37,969
[WHIMPERS]

728
00:30:38,336 --> 00:30:41,005
SOMETHING IS NOT RIGHT.

729
00:30:41,039 --> 00:30:41,673
SHH, SHH,
SHH, SHH.

730
00:30:41,706 --> 00:30:43,174
SHE'S VERY EXCITED.

731
00:30:43,208 --> 00:30:45,977
GREAT CHANGES
ARE HAPPENING
IN HER LIFE.

732
00:30:46,010 --> 00:30:46,744
[WHISPERS]
Be a good girl.

733
00:30:46,778 --> 00:30:49,080
WHO IS IN CHARGE?
I AM IN CHARGE.

734
00:30:49,113 --> 00:30:51,015
YOU WISH TO SEE
THE COURT PAPERS
AGAIN?

735
00:30:51,049 --> 00:30:55,353
NEIN?
 GOOD. WE WILL
 DISCUSS THIS LATER.

736
00:30:57,021 --> 00:30:58,456
Narrator:
GENEVIEVE WAS ALONE,

737
00:30:58,489 --> 00:31:00,692
AND SHE HOWLED IN DESPAIR.

738
00:31:00,725 --> 00:31:03,695
AWOO! AWOO!

739
00:31:03,728 --> 00:31:07,498
MEANWHILE, IN THE DEPOT
WITH NO TIME TO SPARE,

740
00:31:07,532 --> 00:31:09,100
MISS CLAVEL HURRIED FORWARD,

741
00:31:09,133 --> 00:31:11,936
UNAWARE THAT
THE ONE SHE WAS SEEKING

742
00:31:11,970 --> 00:31:13,304
WOULD NOT BE THERE.

743
00:31:13,338 --> 00:31:14,372
Danielle:
VOILÀ!

744
00:31:14,405 --> 00:31:16,140
Chloe:
THERE IS STILL TIME.

745
00:31:16,174 --> 00:31:18,676
[TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWS]

746
00:31:18,710 --> 00:31:20,578
WE MUST RUN!

747
00:31:23,314 --> 00:31:26,217
GIRLS, GIRLS!
KEEP IN LINE.

748
00:31:26,251 --> 00:31:27,151
OH, NEVER MIND.

749
00:31:27,185 --> 00:31:30,488
RUN!
TRÈS VITE!

750
00:31:31,456 --> 00:31:33,725
OH! OH! MONSIEUR.

751
00:31:33,758 --> 00:31:35,560
HAVE YOU SEEN
A LITTLE GIRL

752
00:31:35,593 --> 00:31:37,662
DRESSED LIKE THIS?

753
00:31:37,695 --> 00:31:39,030
WITH AN UNCLE?

754
00:31:39,063 --> 00:31:39,998
AND A DOG?

755
00:31:40,031 --> 00:31:41,032
NON.

756
00:31:41,065 --> 00:31:43,501
IT IS
TRÈS,
TRÈS
 IMPORTANT.

757
00:31:43,534 --> 00:31:44,636
