STOP YAPPING!

999
00:41:38,729 --> 00:41:40,865
DO YOU NOT WANT TO EAT
YOUR LOVELY LUNCH?

1000
00:41:40,898 --> 00:41:44,935
TRÈS BIEN! 
 IT WILL BE TAKEN AWAY!

1001
00:41:44,969 --> 00:41:47,104
All: WE LOVE STALE BREAD

1002
00:41:47,137 --> 00:41:49,073
WITHOUT THE BUTTER.

1003
00:41:49,106 --> 00:41:51,609
BUT AT LEAST
WE HAVE EACH OTHER.

1004
00:41:51,642 --> 00:41:54,345
BEFORE, AT
YOUR WONDERFUL SCHOOL,

1005
00:41:54,378 --> 00:41:55,246
YOU HAD A PET?

1006
00:41:55,279 --> 00:41:57,882
OUI.
 ALL OF US
 HAD GENEVIEVE,

1007
00:41:57,915 --> 00:42:00,117
THE BEST DOG
IN PARIS.

1008
00:42:00,150 --> 00:42:03,821
IF ONLY I KNEW
SHE WERE SAFE.

1009
00:42:09,226 --> 00:42:11,962
MADAME, THE POLICE ARTIST.

1010
00:42:11,996 --> 00:42:14,832
UH, PLEASE TELL ME
ABOUT THE SUSPECT,

1011
00:42:14,865 --> 00:42:16,333
THIS, UH, UNCLE HORST.

1012
00:42:16,367 --> 00:42:20,137
MONSIEUR HORST
WAS TALL, ELEGANT.

1013
00:42:20,170 --> 00:42:22,239
Narrator: MISS CLAVEL
CHOSE HER WORDS

1014
00:42:22,273 --> 00:42:24,308
AND DESCRIBED HORST
WITH CARE,

1015
00:42:24,341 --> 00:42:27,111
WHILE THE ARTIST
WAS SKETCHING

1016
00:42:27,144 --> 00:42:29,013
WITH TALENTED FLAIR.

1017
00:42:29,046 --> 00:42:31,315
VOILÀ!

1018
00:42:31,348 --> 00:42:32,650
UH, NO.

1019
00:42:32,683 --> 00:42:34,785
HIS HAIR,
IT WAS WAVY,

1020
00:42:34,818 --> 00:42:36,854
RATHER LIGHT.

1021
00:42:40,891 --> 00:42:42,893
AH.COMME ÇA!

1022
00:42:42,927 --> 00:42:44,795
[GASPS]
OH, NO, NO.

1023
00:42:44,828 --> 00:42:47,798
HIS FACE--
A LITTLE LONGER.

1024
00:42:49,967 --> 00:42:51,068
[GASPS]

1025
00:42:51,101 --> 00:42:52,803
N-NOT QUITE.

1026
00:42:52,836 --> 00:42:53,804
OH, DEAR.

1027
00:42:53,837 --> 00:42:58,108
I'M NOT SURE
THIS IS HELPING
FIND OUR MADELINE.

1028
00:43:00,911 --> 00:43:03,380
Narrator: AT EACH METRO
STATION ALONG THE ROUTE,

1029
00:43:03,414 --> 00:43:07,051
GENEVIEVE
SNIFFED FOR A CLUE.

1030
00:43:11,689 --> 00:43:14,959
BUT WHEN THEIR TIME
WAS RUNNING OUT...

1031
00:43:14,992 --> 00:43:16,827
Girls: AHH.

1032
00:43:16,860 --> 00:43:18,395
THEY HAD TO DECIDE
WHAT TO DO.

1033
00:43:18,429 --> 00:43:21,765
NEXT STOP IS THE LAST.
MAYBE THERE.

1034
00:43:21,799 --> 00:43:22,833
IT IS TOO LATE.

1035
00:43:22,866 --> 00:43:25,869
WE MUST GET BACK
BEFORE MISS CLAVEL.

1036
00:43:25,903 --> 00:43:27,204
TOMORROW, THEN?

1037
00:43:27,237 --> 00:43:29,907
Girls: TOMORROW!

1038
00:43:32,142 --> 00:43:33,911
Narrator: AS THEY LEFT,
THEY WONDERED

1039
00:43:33,944 --> 00:43:36,981
HOW MADELINE
WAS DOING NOW.

1040
00:43:37,014 --> 00:43:38,415
I HOPE
SHE'S ALL RIGHT.

1041
00:43:38,449 --> 00:43:39,850
I HOPE SHE'S NOT SICK.

1042
00:43:39,883 --> 00:43:41,251
I HOPE SHE'S NOT COLD.

1043
00:43:41,285 --> 00:43:42,319
I HOPE
SHE'S NOT HUNGRY.

1044
00:43:42,353 --> 00:43:45,189
PAUVRE
 MADELINE.

1045
00:43:45,823 --> 00:43:47,925
Narrator: WHEN THEY HEARD
THE FACTORY CLOCK,

1046
00:43:47,958 --> 00:43:51,695
THE GIRLS LINED UP
TO FACE LA CROQUE.

1047
00:43:51,729 --> 00:43:52,830
I'LL TAKE THAT!

1048
00:43:52,863 --> 00:43:55,165
THERE ARE
A LOT MORE ANTIQUES

1049
00:43:55,199 --> 00:43:57,668
TO BE DONE TOMORROW.

1050
00:44:00,938 --> 00:44:01,872
LOOK WHAT YOU'VE DONE!

1051
00:44:01,905 --> 00:44:05,442
ALL YOUR COUGHING HAS
TURNED THE LACE YELLOW!

1052
00:44:05,476 --> 00:44:06,310
RUINED!

1053
00:44:06,343 --> 00:44:08,178
I'M S-S-SORRY.

1054
00:44:08,212 --> 00:44:09,947
FROM NOW ON--

1055
00:44:09,980 --> 00:44:11,915
MADAME, PLEASE, NO.

1056
00:44:11,949 --> 00:44:13,384
I WILL BE CAREFUL.

1057
00:44:13,417 --> 00:44:14,985
I WILL NOT COUGH.

1058
00:44:15,019 --> 00:44:16,253
[COUGHS]

1059
00:44:16,286 --> 00:44:19,089
YOU WILL WORK
ONLY ON...

1060
00:44:19,123 --> 00:44:21,158
BLACK LACE!

1061
00:44:21,191 --> 00:44:22,092
OH, NO!

1062
00:44:22,126 --> 00:44:25,129
I WON'T HAVE
MY PRECIOUS WHITES
DISCOLORED!

1063
00:44:25,162 --> 00:44:28,065
REMEMBER THAT,
ALL OF YOU!

1064
00:44:28,098 --> 00:44:28,999
[ALL GASP]

1065
00:44:29,033 --> 00:44:30,467
WHAT IS WRONG?

1066
00:44:30,501 --> 00:44:31,435
WITH NO LIGHT,

1067
00:44:31,468 --> 00:44:33,771
WORKING
ON THE BLACK LACE,

1068
00:44:33,804 --> 00:44:35,439
IT TAKES OUR EYES.

1069
00:44:35,472 --> 00:44:37,808
MY GRANDMAMA
TURNED BLIND THAT WAY.

1070
00:44:37,841 --> 00:44:39,843
YOU CAN'T DO THAT
TO FIFI!

1071
00:44:39,877 --> 00:44:42,146
IT IS HEARTLESS
AND CRUEL!

1072
00:44:42,179 --> 00:44:43,313
SHE IS SICK!

1073
00:44:43,347 --> 00:44:45,916
I BEG YOUR PARDON.

1074
00:44:45,949 --> 00:44:49,820
SHE NEEDS SUNLIGHT.
SHE NEEDS MORE FOOD.

1075
00:44:49,853 --> 00:44:50,521
SHE NEEDS--

1076
00:44:50,554 --> 00:44:52,990
WHAT YOU NEED
IS A LESSON!

1077
00:44:53,023 --> 00:44:54,992
SILENCE!

1078
00:44:56,560 --> 00:44:57,961
UHH!

1079
00:44:57,995 --> 00:45:01,465
SPOILED BRATS
HAVE TO LEARN
THE HARD WAY!

1080
00:45:01,498 --> 00:45:04,468
AND YOU ARE
THE BEST TEACHER.

1081
00:45:04,501 --> 00:45:06,870
[BOTH LAUGH]

1082
00:45:06,904 --> 00:45:10,007
I DON'T SEE
WHAT IS SO FUNNY.

1083
00:45:10,841 --> 00:45:11,975
[SIGHS]

1084
00:45:12,009 --> 00:45:13,977
OH, MAMA.

1085
00:45:14,011 --> 00:45:16,313
[SNIFFLES]

1086
00:45:21,318 --> 00:45:26,056
♪ HERE I SIT
SO COLD AND HUNGRY ♪

1087
00:45:26,090 --> 00:45:30,894
♪ FEELING LOST
AND FAR AWAY ♪

1088
00:45:30,928 --> 00:45:34,798
♪ HAPPINESS
IS JUST A MEMORY ♪

1089
00:45:34,832 --> 00:45:41,305
♪ A PATCH OF SUN
FROM YESTERDAY ♪

1090
00:45:41,905 --> 00:45:46,877
♪ WHERE IS THE HOPE
THAT I ONCE KNEW? ♪

1091
00:45:46,910 --> 00:45:50,347
♪ MY DREAMS HAVE VANISHED

1092
00:45:50,380 --> 00:45:52,483
♪ IT IS TRUE

1093
00:45:52,516 --> 00:45:57,821
♪ WHEN WILL THE SUN
COME SHINING THROUGH? ♪

1094
00:45:57,855 --> 00:46:00,924
♪ WHERE IS THE HOPE

1095
00:46:00,958 --> 00:46:05,262
♪ THAT I ONCE KNEW?

1096
00:46:12,002 --> 00:46:16,039
♪ FRIENDS WOULD CALL ME
"BRAVEST LION" ♪

1097
00:46:16,073 --> 00:46:20,177
♪ I ONCE HAD
THAT KIND OF ROAR ♪

1098
00:46:20,210 --> 00:46:24,882
♪ IF I REACH INSIDE
FOR COURAGE ♪

1099
00:46:24,915 --> 00:46:29,319
♪ PERHAPS I CAN
BE STRONG ONCE MORE ♪

1100
00:46:29,353 --> 00:46:34,424
♪ I'LL FIND THE HOPE
THAT I ONCE KNEW ♪

1101
00:46:34,458 --> 00:46:39,997
♪ AND I WILL MAKE
MY DREAMS COME TRUE ♪

1102
00:46:40,030 --> 00:46:45,335
♪ I'LL SEE THE SUN
COME SHINING THROUGH ♪

1103
00:46:45,369 --> 00:46:48,539
♪ FULL OF THE HOPE

1104
00:46:48,572 --> 00:46:50,607
♪ THAT I ONCE KNEW

1105
00:46:50,641 --> 00:46:54,912
Factory girls:
♪ WE'LL FIND THE HOPE
THAT WE ONCE KNEW ♪

1106
00:46:54,945 --> 00:46:59,049
♪ AND WE WILL MAKE
OUR DREAMS COME TRUE ♪

1107
00:46:59,082 --> 00:47:03,320
♪ WE'LL SEE THE SUN
COME SHINING THROUGH ♪

1108
00:47:03,353 --> 00:47:04,154
FIFI!

1109
00:47:04,188 --> 00:47:07,157
♪ FULL OF THE HOPE

1110
00:47:07,191 --> 00:47:14,965
♪ THAT WE ONCE KNEW

1111
00:47:17,968 --> 00:47:20,470
FIFI? ARE YOU THERE?

1112
00:47:20,504 --> 00:47:22,639
MADELINE,
WE WERE WORRIED.

1113
00:47:22,673 --> 00:47:24,174
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

1114
00:47:24,208 --> 00:47:24,942
MAIS OUI.

1115
00:47:24,975 --> 00:47:29,012
FIFI, I'VE DECIDED
WE MUST ESCAPE.

1116
00:47:29,046 --> 00:47:31,481
AH, THAT
IS NOT SO EASY.

1117
00:47:31,515 --> 00:47:34,284
I TRIED. [COUGHS]

1118
00:47:34,318 --> 00:47:35,252
AS PUNISHMENT,

1119
00:47:35,285 --> 00:47:36,653
LA CROQUE
CUT OFF MY HAIR

1120
00:47:36,687 --> 00:47:38,422
TO MAKE BLACK LACE.

1121
00:47:38,455 --> 00:47:40,457
WHY IS LA CROQUE
SO HORRIBLE?

1122
00:47:40,490 --> 00:47:43,427
THEY SAY SHE WAS
A CABARET STAR ONCE.

1123
00:47:43,460 --> 00:47:46,196
[CANCAN MUSIC PLAYS]

1124
00:47:46,230 --> 00:47:49,299
Fifi: THEN
SOMETHING HAPPENED.

1125
00:47:50,133 --> 00:47:53,203
Narrator: FIFI EXPLAINED
THAT LA CROQUE WAS A DANCER

1126
00:47:53,237 --> 00:47:56,607
WHOSE KICKS
DAZZLED ALL OF PARIS.

1127
00:47:57,574 --> 00:48:01,545
AND ONE FATAL NIGHT
THROUGH A "SEAMING" MISCHANCE...

1128
00:48:01,578 --> 00:48:03,981
[FABRIC RIPS]

1129
00:48:04,014 --> 00:48:06,116
[ALL LAUGHING]

1130
00:48:09,052 --> 00:48:10,520
UHH! [CRASH]

1131
00:48:10,554 --> 00:48:11,388
[ALL GASP]

1132
00:48:11,421 --> 00:48:15,425
Narrator: HER FAME
ENDED MOST TRAGICALLY.

1133
00:48:15,759 --> 00:48:16,460
ALORS?

1134
00:48:16,493 --> 00:48:18,562
THEN SHE COULD
NO LONGER PERFORM

1135
00:48:18,595 --> 00:48:20,964
BECAUSE SHE FELT
SO HUMILIATED.

1136
00:48:20,998 --> 00:48:22,633
QUEL DOMMAGE!

1137
00:48:22,666 --> 00:48:23,533
SHE HAD NO MONEY,

1138
00:48:23,567 --> 00:48:26,003
SO SHE SOLD
HER LONG HAIR
TO MAKE LACE.

1139
00:48:26,036 --> 00:48:28,005
NOW SHE RUNS
THE FACTORY.

1140
00:48:28,038 --> 00:48:28,872
[COUGHS]

1141
00:48:28,905 --> 00:48:31,208
AND SHE WILL CUT OFF
YOUR HAIR LIKE MINE

1142
00:48:31,241 --> 00:48:32,442
IF YOU MAKE TROUBLE.

1143
00:48:32,476 --> 00:48:33,543
IT WILL GROW BACK.

1144
00:48:33,577 --> 00:48:35,045
I WILL TAKE THE CHANCE.

1145
00:48:35,078 --> 00:48:36,713
I WILL FIND A WAY OUT.

1146
00:48:36,747 --> 00:48:38,649
YOU ARE
NOT SCARED?

1147
00:48:38,682 --> 00:48:40,017
I AM ANGRY.

1148
00:48:40,050 --> 00:48:41,218
MOI AUSSI.

1149
00:48:41,251 --> 00:48:43,987
WE HAVE NO FAMILY,
NONE OF US.

1150
00:48:44,021 --> 00:48:46,490
LA CROQUE AND HENRI
LIE TO THE COURTS.

1151
00:48:46,523 --> 00:48:48,592
THEY SAY THEY WILL
TAKE CARE OF US,

1152
00:48:48,625 --> 00:48:51,094
THEN TREAT US
 LIKE THIS.

1153
00:48:51,128 --> 00:48:52,496
DON'T WORRY, FIFI.

1154
00:48:52,529 --> 00:48:54,665
WE CAN LOOK
AFTER EACH OTHER.

1155
00:48:54,698 --> 00:48:56,366
LIKE REAL FRIENDS?

1156
00:48:56,400 --> 00:48:57,668
BETTER.

1157
00:48:57,701 --> 00:48:59,102
LIKE FAMILY.

1158
00:48:59,136 --> 00:48:59,703
FAMILY?

1159
00:48:59,736 --> 00:49:02,239
YOU REALLY THINK SO?

1160
00:49:02,272 --> 00:49:04,107
I KNOW SO.

1161
00:49:04,808 --> 00:49:06,376
[MOUSE SQUEAKS]

1162
00:49:06,677 --> 00:49:09,713
[GIRLS LAUGH]

1163
00:49:09,746 --> 00:49:11,615
[THUNDER]

1164
00:49:11,648 --> 00:49:14,718
BOTHERSOME BRAT.

1165
00:49:16,219 --> 00:49:18,021
[THUNDER]

1166
00:49:25,662 --> 00:49:27,664
DO NOT LOSE HEART,
MES PETITES.

1167
00:49:27,698 --> 00:49:30,334
WE WILL FIND
OUR MADELINE.

1168
00:49:30,367 --> 00:49:31,768
WHERE COULD SHE BE?

1169
00:49:31,802 --> 00:49:34,271
I HOPE SHE
IS NOT LONELY...

1170
00:49:34,304 --> 00:49:35,639
[THUNDER]

1171
00:49:35,672 --> 00:49:37,040
OR HUNGRY...

1172
00:49:37,074 --> 00:49:39,543
[WATER SPLASHING]

1173
00:49:40,077 --> 00:49:41,778
OR WET AND COLD.

1174
00:49:41,812 --> 00:49:44,047
SHE KNOWS
WE LOVE HER.

1175
00:49:44,081 --> 00:49:44,748
THAT IS TRUE.

1176
00:49:44,781 --> 00:49:46,783
AND WE WILL BE
LOOKING FOR HER.

1177
00:49:46,817 --> 00:49:50,687
TOMORROW I WILL
GO AGAIN WITH
THE GENDARMES.

1178
00:49:50,721 --> 00:49:51,755
MAIS CERTAINMENT!

1179
00:49:51,788 --> 00:49:53,790
Miss Clavel:
AND WE WON'T GIVE UP...

1180
00:49:53,824 --> 00:49:56,393
Girls: TILL WE FIND HER!

1181
00:49:56,426 --> 00:49:57,194
EXACTLY!

1182
00:49:57,227 --> 00:49:59,229
BONNE NUIT,
MES CHERIES.

1183
00:49:59,262 --> 00:50:02,165
Girls: SLEEP WELL,
MISS CLAVEL.

1184
00:50:02,199 --> 00:50:05,235
Narrator: THEIR HEARTS
WERE WITH MADELINE.

1185
00:50:05,268 --> 00:50:06,336
WHERE WAS SHE NOW?

1186
00:50:06,370 --> 00:50:07,738
AND THEY PRAYED
THAT THE NEXT DAY

1187
00:50:07,771 --> 00:50:10,173
THEY'D FIND HER SOMEHOW.

1188
00:50:22,185 --> 00:50:23,720
Mrs. Murphy: BYE-BYE!

1189
00:50:24,888 --> 00:50:25,655
AH!

1190
00:50:25,689 --> 00:50:27,691
Narrator: MISS CLAVEL
LEFT THE HOUSE

1191
00:50:27,724 --> 00:50:30,227
JUST THE SAME AS BEFORE...

1192
00:50:30,260 --> 00:50:32,462
BUT THE CHILDREN
DID NOT EXPECT

1193
00:50:32,496 --> 00:50:33,663
WHAT LAY IN STORE.

1194
00:50:33,697 --> 00:50:34,798
[GASPS]
[GASPS]

1195
00:50:34,831 --> 00:50:37,667
[CAT GROWLS]

1196
00:50:37,701 --> 00:50:39,603
[MRREERW]

1197
00:50:39,636 --> 00:50:40,303
¡CARAMBA!

1198
00:50:40,337 --> 00:50:43,507
SHE'S BORROWED
MY MOTHER'S CAT.

1199
00:50:44,474 --> 00:50:45,342
WHAT TO DO?

1200
00:50:45,375 --> 00:50:46,710
¡JASE!
 I KNOW!

1201
00:50:46,743 --> 00:50:50,113
Narrator:
WHILE PEPITO RAN OFF
FOR THE THING HE FORGOT,

1202
00:50:50,147 --> 00:50:53,817
CLEVER MADELINE TRIED
A NEW LACE-MAKING KNOT.

1203
00:50:53,850 --> 00:50:57,154
[BOBBINS CLACKING]

1204
00:50:59,356 --> 00:51:00,791
[FOOTSTEPS]

1205
00:51:02,225 --> 00:51:05,128
Narrator:
AS THE FACTORY VILLAINS
INSPECTED THE WORK,

1206
00:51:05,162 --> 00:51:09,666
IT WAS MADAME LA CROQUE
WHO FIRST SPOTTED A QUIRK.

1207
00:51:10,267 --> 00:51:11,334
REGARDEZ!

1208
00:51:11,368 --> 00:51:13,303
I CAN READ.

1209
00:51:13,603 --> 00:51:16,573
La Croque:
COME UP HERE! ALL OF YOU!

1210
00:51:17,908 --> 00:51:18,708
AHA!

1211
00:51:18,742 --> 00:51:20,710
La Croque: HELP...

1212
00:51:20,744 --> 00:51:24,214
I AM A PRISONER...

1213
00:51:24,247 --> 00:51:26,450
IN A...

1214
00:51:26,483 --> 00:51:27,784
LACE FACTORY.

1215
00:51:27,818 --> 00:51:33,623
YOU WILL STAND HERE
ALL DAY, ALL NIGHT,

1216
00:51:33,657 --> 00:51:36,626
ALL YEAR
TILL I FIND OUT

1217
00:51:36,660 --> 00:51:40,831
WHO'S RESPONSIBLE
FOR THIS SACRILEGE.

1218
00:51:40,864 --> 00:51:43,467
PERHAPS A FLAW
IN THE THREAD, MADAME?

1219
00:51:43,500 --> 00:51:45,869
THINK
THIS IS A HOLIDAY?

1220
00:51:46,703 --> 00:51:49,506
GET BACK TO
YOUR BOBBINS, BRATS.

1221
00:51:49,539 --> 00:51:51,241
[GASPS] [GASPS]

1222
00:51:56,613 --> 00:51:59,749
Narrator:
LA CROQUE AND HENRI
MADE THEIR WAY TO THE TOP

1223
00:51:59,783 --> 00:52:03,920
AS MADELINE PLANNED
A SURPRISE FOR THE SHOP.

1224
00:52:05,222 --> 00:52:07,457
Narrator:
BACK AT THE OLD HOUSE,
PEPITO POPPED IN

1225
00:52:07,491 --> 00:52:11,728
WITH SOMETHING TO GIVE
AN OLD TRICK A NEW SPIN.

1226
00:52:15,432 --> 00:52:18,635
[MRREEERW]

1227
00:52:18,969 --> 00:52:19,903
[HISS]

1228
00:52:19,936 --> 00:52:21,872
[RREEER]

1229
00:52:22,906 --> 00:52:24,808
[RREEER]

1230
00:52:24,841 --> 00:52:26,343
[RREEER]

1231
00:52:26,376 --> 00:52:26,977
AAH!

1232
00:52:27,010 --> 00:52:28,879
AAH! GET OFF!
GET OFF ME!

1233
00:52:28,912 --> 00:52:29,746
OW, GET AWAY
FROM ME!

1234
00:52:29,779 --> 00:52:32,682
GET OFF!
OH, OW, OOH, AAH!

1235
00:52:32,716 --> 00:52:33,683
OH HO, NO!

1236
00:52:33,717 --> 00:52:34,584
GET AWAY!

1237
00:52:34,618 --> 00:52:36,720
Narrator: POOR MRS. MURPHY
WAS IN DISTRESS.

1238
00:52:36,753 --> 00:52:39,990
PEPITO'S PLAN
WAS A SUCCESS.

1239
00:52:40,023 --> 00:52:42,492
¡PERFECTO!

1240
00:52:47,864 --> 00:52:49,432
[BOBBINS CLACKING]

