HE IS THE MAN?

1486
01:02:45,962 --> 01:02:47,797
OUI!

1487
01:02:51,901 --> 01:02:55,104
[SARCASTICALLY]
AW, YOU ALWAYS
PLAY WITH DOLLIES

1488
01:02:55,138 --> 01:02:57,273
AND WEAR
THE LITTLE DRESS?

1489
01:02:57,306 --> 01:02:58,541
[DOLL CRIES]

1490
01:02:58,574 --> 01:03:00,143
[GIGGLES]

1491
01:03:01,210 --> 01:03:03,112
TELL US
WHERE MADELINE IS!

1492
01:03:03,146 --> 01:03:07,483
IF YOU DO NOT,
IT WILL GO
VERY HARD ON YOU.

1493
01:03:07,517 --> 01:03:08,384
MMM!

1494
01:03:08,417 --> 01:03:12,922
IF HE IS SILENT,
HOW DO WE FIND
MADELINE?

1495
01:03:17,894 --> 01:03:18,995
WHAT NOW?

1496
01:03:19,028 --> 01:03:19,862
[WOOF]

1497
01:03:19,896 --> 01:03:21,430
LOOK AT GENEVIEVE!

1498
01:03:21,464 --> 01:03:23,099
[WOOF WOOF]

1499
01:03:23,132 --> 01:03:24,867
[PANTING]

1500
01:03:28,437 --> 01:03:30,973
NOBODY
IS THERE.

1501
01:03:37,446 --> 01:03:38,948
[GASPS]

1502
01:03:39,916 --> 01:03:41,951
MADELINE!

1503
01:03:43,619 --> 01:03:46,489
VOILA.
 HUH?

1504
01:03:46,689 --> 01:03:50,993
YOU DO NOT GET OFF
SO EASILY.

1505
01:03:51,027 --> 01:03:52,528
[GASPS]

1506
01:03:54,964 --> 01:03:55,898
[GASPS]

1507
01:03:55,932 --> 01:03:57,200
AAH! OOF!

1508
01:03:57,233 --> 01:03:58,868
NOW!

1509
01:04:01,671 --> 01:04:03,339
WHY, YOU...

1510
01:04:03,372 --> 01:04:05,975
UN MONSTRE.

1511
01:04:06,008 --> 01:04:08,878
[GASPS]
POOR MADELINE.

1512
01:04:09,212 --> 01:04:11,013
AY AY AY!

1513
01:04:13,082 --> 01:04:14,317
¡BUENO!

1514
01:04:14,350 --> 01:04:16,118
STOP!

1515
01:04:16,152 --> 01:04:17,987
STOP, I SAY!

1516
01:04:18,020 --> 01:04:20,489
WHEN I GET
OUT OF THIS,

1517
01:04:20,523 --> 01:04:24,961
THERE WILL
BE HAIRCUTS
FOR EVERYONE.

1518
01:04:24,994 --> 01:04:25,595
[NERVOUS CHATTERING]

1519
01:04:25,628 --> 01:04:28,464
GUESS WHERE
I'LL BEGIN.

1520
01:04:29,165 --> 01:04:31,467
NO ONE CAN
GET DOWN HERE...

1521
01:04:31,500 --> 01:04:32,468
TO HELP YOU.

1522
01:04:32,501 --> 01:04:34,370
Narrator: WHILE MADELINE'S
FATE HUNG BY A THREAD,

1523
01:04:34,403 --> 01:04:36,439
HER FRIEND PEPITO
WAS PLANNING AHEAD.

1524
01:04:36,472 --> 01:04:39,976
La Croque: THAT'S
THE OLDEST TRICK
IN THE WORLD.

1525
01:04:40,009 --> 01:04:41,644
THINK
I'LL LOOK BACK?

1526
01:04:41,677 --> 01:04:43,546
[CHUCKLES]
THINK AGAIN!

1527
01:04:43,579 --> 01:04:47,216
THERE IS NO ESCAPE.

1528
01:04:47,516 --> 01:04:49,418
Narrator: WHILE HENRI'S
CROOKED ACT WAS THROUGH,

1529
01:04:49,452 --> 01:04:53,022
IN MISS CLAVEL'S MIND,
THERE WAS STILL MUCH TO DO.

1530
01:04:53,055 --> 01:04:56,559
IF ONLY THERE
WERE JUST A CLUE...

1531
01:04:56,592 --> 01:04:59,161
MONSIEUR, SURELY,
IF YOU HELP,

1532
01:04:59,195 --> 01:05:02,231
THE COURTS WILL NOT
BE SO HARD ON YOU.

1533
01:05:02,265 --> 01:05:03,966
WHAT IS IT
YOU ARE SAYING?

1534
01:05:04,000 --> 01:05:06,235
THEY WILL GIVE YOU
A LIGHTER SENTENCE

1535
01:05:06,269 --> 01:05:09,438
IF YOU LEAD US
TO MADELINE.

1536
01:05:10,139 --> 01:05:12,975
YOU CAN PROMISE THIS?

1537
01:05:13,009 --> 01:05:14,710
HMM.

1538
01:05:14,744 --> 01:05:16,746
ALL RIGHT.
I'LL TELL YOU.

1539
01:05:16,779 --> 01:05:20,249
I THINK YOU WILL
LEAD US THERE.

1540
01:05:23,619 --> 01:05:26,289
[MADELINE LAUGHS]

1541
01:05:27,356 --> 01:05:28,291
[LAUGHS]

1542
01:05:28,324 --> 01:05:29,158
LAUGHTER?

1543
01:05:29,191 --> 01:05:32,528
YOU WILL NEVER LAUGH
AT LA CROQUE AGAIN.

1544
01:05:32,561 --> 01:05:34,563
Narrator:
LUCKILY FOR MADELINE,

1545
01:05:34,597 --> 01:05:37,266
PEPITO ACTED JUST IN TIME.

1546
01:05:38,668 --> 01:05:39,669
UNH!

1547
01:05:39,702 --> 01:05:41,203
AAH!

1548
01:05:41,237 --> 01:05:43,272
[LAUGHING]

1549
01:05:43,306 --> 01:05:45,641
OHH!

1550
01:05:46,542 --> 01:05:47,743
[LA CROQUE GASPS]

1551
01:05:47,777 --> 01:05:49,111
AAH!

1552
01:05:49,145 --> 01:05:50,613
OHH!

1553
01:05:51,781 --> 01:05:53,749
HELP! GET IT AWAY FROM ME!

1554
01:05:53,783 --> 01:05:55,651
Narrator: AS LA CROQUE
TRAPPED HERSELF

1555
01:05:55,685 --> 01:05:56,786
IN THE LACE ON THE FLOOR,

1556
01:05:56,819 --> 01:05:59,655
FIFI RUSHED OFF
WITH THE KEY TO THE DOOR.

1557
01:05:59,689 --> 01:06:04,026
HURRY! WE MUST
HELP MADELINE!

1558
01:06:06,696 --> 01:06:09,131
HURRY! TIE HER UP!

1559
01:06:09,165 --> 01:06:13,703
Narrator: THE GIRLS AND PEPITO
DASHED INTO THE SHOP

1560
01:06:13,736 --> 01:06:16,739
JUST AS THE GENDARMES
PULLED UP TO A STOP.

1561
01:06:16,772 --> 01:06:19,375
La Croque:
HORRIBLE CHILDREN!

1562
01:06:19,408 --> 01:06:22,678
MADELINE, YOU ARE
THE WORST OF ALL!

1563
01:06:22,712 --> 01:06:26,649
VOILA!
 MY ANGEL.

1564
01:06:28,084 --> 01:06:30,252
[KIDS CHATTERING]

1565
01:06:30,286 --> 01:06:31,320
UNH!

1566
01:06:31,354 --> 01:06:32,488
ARGH!

1567
01:06:32,521 --> 01:06:34,557
MADELINE!

1568
01:06:35,324 --> 01:06:37,560
MISS CLAVEL!

1569
01:06:40,229 --> 01:06:41,163
Girls: AWW!

1570
01:06:41,197 --> 01:06:42,164
MY LITTLE ONE.

1571
01:06:42,198 --> 01:06:46,635
MES
 ENFANTS, WHAT
 ARE YOU DOING HERE?

1572
01:06:46,669 --> 01:06:48,738
RESCUING MADELINE!

1573
01:06:48,771 --> 01:06:51,207
[GRUNTS]
[GRUNTS]

1574
01:06:51,240 --> 01:06:51,807
HENRI?

1575
01:06:51,841 --> 01:06:54,477
[LAUGHS NERVOUSLY]

1576
01:06:54,510 --> 01:06:56,779
YOU RAT!

1577
01:06:56,812 --> 01:06:58,247
IT WAS
ALL HIS IDEA.

1578
01:06:58,280 --> 01:06:59,715
IT WAS HIS SCHEME!

1579
01:06:59,749 --> 01:07:01,517
EVERYTHING!

1580
01:07:01,550 --> 01:07:02,218
OOH!

1581
01:07:02,251 --> 01:07:05,688
La Croque:
OOH, LET ME AT HIM.

1582
01:07:06,355 --> 01:07:08,491
Narrator: AND THEN
AT THAT INSTANT,

1583
01:07:08,524 --> 01:07:10,626
HENRI TOOK FLIGHT.

1584
01:07:12,495 --> 01:07:13,295
[BLOWS WHISTLE]

1585
01:07:13,329 --> 01:07:14,764
Narrator: AS THE GENDARMES
PURSUED HIM,

1586
01:07:14,797 --> 01:07:17,533
HE DODGED LEFT AND RIGHT.

1587
01:07:17,566 --> 01:07:19,301
THEN LA CROQUE
JOINED THE CHASE

1588
01:07:19,335 --> 01:07:20,703
WITH A WELL-POINTED KICK...

1589
01:07:20,736 --> 01:07:21,637
HA!
AAH!

1590
01:07:21,670 --> 01:07:25,241
AND PEPITO PERFORMED
AN OLD ARGENTINE TRICK.

1591
01:07:25,274 --> 01:07:27,243
Pepito:
¡ARRIBA!

1592
01:07:27,276 --> 01:07:28,611
WHOA-AAH!

1593
01:07:28,644 --> 01:07:29,779
¡OLE!

1594
01:07:29,812 --> 01:07:31,313
WHOA-OH! OW!

1595
01:07:31,347 --> 01:07:32,114
OOF!

1596
01:07:32,148 --> 01:07:34,417
Girls: YAH! UNH!

1597
01:07:34,450 --> 01:07:35,418
DAAH!

1598
01:07:35,451 --> 01:07:39,688
A FITTING CURTAIN
FOR A COWARD.

1599
01:07:39,722 --> 01:07:40,723
[GASPS]

1600
01:07:40,756 --> 01:07:41,891
[GIRLS LAUGH]

1601
01:07:41,924 --> 01:07:42,858
All: YAY!

1602
01:07:42,892 --> 01:07:44,727
[LAUGHING]
[LAUGHING]

1603
01:07:44,760 --> 01:07:46,729
THERE WILL BE
A SUBSTANTIAL REWARD

1604
01:07:46,762 --> 01:07:49,398
FOR THE CAPTURE
OF THIS ONE.

1605
01:07:49,432 --> 01:07:52,735
Narrator: THE GENDARMES
LED THE VILLAINS AWAY.

1606
01:07:52,768 --> 01:07:55,237
THEIR MISDEEDS WERE ENDED.

1607
01:07:55,271 --> 01:07:56,739
NOW THEY WOULD PAY.

1608
01:07:56,772 --> 01:08:00,342
MY BRAVE MADELINE.

1609
01:08:01,777 --> 01:08:02,778
I WAS BRAVE

1610
01:08:02,812 --> 01:08:07,349
BECAUSE I HAD FRIENDS
ALL AROUND ME.

1611
01:08:07,883 --> 01:08:10,352
VOICI.
 LOOK.

1612
01:08:11,353 --> 01:08:12,721
MAMA'S BEADS!

1613
01:08:12,755 --> 01:08:15,891
ALL OF THEM.
EACH AND EVERY ONE.

1614
01:08:15,925 --> 01:08:18,861
[GIRLS CHATTERING]

1615
01:08:19,495 --> 01:08:20,896
YOU WERE RIGHT,
MISS CLAVEL.

1616
01:08:20,930 --> 01:08:24,867
FAMILIES COME IN ALL
SHAPES AND SIZES.

1617
01:08:24,900 --> 01:08:28,704
AND NOW
I WANT TO GO HOME.

1618
01:08:28,737 --> 01:08:29,839
[WOOF]

1619
01:08:29,872 --> 01:08:31,807
Miss Clavel:
OUI,
 MADELINE.

1620
01:08:31,841 --> 01:08:35,344
HOME SOUNDS GOOD, NO?

1621
01:08:35,377 --> 01:08:37,746
[GIGGLES]

1622
01:08:39,415 --> 01:08:40,850
Narrator:
THE VERY NEXT MORNING,

1623
01:08:40,883 --> 01:08:42,485
THE OLD HOUSE
WAS CHEERFUL,

1624
01:08:42,518 --> 01:08:45,721
THOUGH MADELINE'S HAIRCUT
WAS STILL A BIT FEARFUL.

1625
01:08:45,754 --> 01:08:47,857
AS THE GIRLS
LEFT THE HOUSE,

1626
01:08:47,890 --> 01:08:50,292
MISS CLAVEL WAS IN SHOCK...

1627
01:08:50,326 --> 01:08:51,327
[GASPS]

1628
01:08:51,360 --> 01:08:54,697
WHEN SHE SAW THEY HAD ALL
COPIED MADELINE'S LOCKS.

1629
01:08:54,730 --> 01:08:56,265
[GASPS]

1630
01:08:58,868 --> 01:08:59,602
[CHUCKLES]

1631
01:08:59,635 --> 01:09:03,405
TRÈS BIEN, 
 LITTLE GIRLS.

1632
01:09:03,439 --> 01:09:04,406
WE ARE THANKFUL

1633
01:09:04,440 --> 01:09:09,678
THAT MADELINE
IS BACK WITH US
SAFE AND SOUND.

1634
01:09:09,712 --> 01:09:10,813
Girls:
OUI, OUI!

1635
01:09:10,846 --> 01:09:12,781
BONNE NUIT,
MES PETITES.

1636
01:09:12,815 --> 01:09:14,783
I HOPE
YOU SLEEP WELL.

1637
01:09:14,817 --> 01:09:19,755
Girls: GOOD NIGHT, GOOD NIGHT,
DEAR MISS CLAVEL.

1638
01:09:20,689 --> 01:09:23,259
YOU ARE LUCKY
TO RECEIVE SUCH
A LARGE REWARD

1639
01:09:23,292 --> 01:09:25,661
FOR CAPTURING
THOSE THIEVES,
MADELINE.

1640
01:09:25,694 --> 01:09:27,563
OUI,
 THAT IS TRUE.

1641
01:09:27,596 --> 01:09:29,798
I KNOW WHAT I WOULD DO
WITH THE REWARD MONEY.

1642
01:09:29,832 --> 01:09:34,837
ME, TOO! I WOULD GO
SHOPPING FOR WONDERFUL
CLOTHES AND JEWELRY.

1643
01:09:34,870 --> 01:09:39,808
AND TRAVEL AROUND THE WORLD
TO EXOTIC COUNTRIES.

1644
01:09:39,842 --> 01:09:41,710
I WOULD HAVE
A PRIVATE ZOO

1645
01:09:41,744 --> 01:09:43,746
WITH ALL OF
MY FAVORITE ANIMALS.

1646
01:09:43,779 --> 01:09:46,916
OUI,
 THOSE ARE
 TEMPTING CHOICES,

1647
01:09:46,949 --> 01:09:51,253
BUT I HAVE SOMETHING
VERY SPECIAL IN MIND.

1648
01:09:51,820 --> 01:09:55,891
Narrator: AT LAST IT ARRIVED,
THAT WONDERFUL DAY

1649
01:09:55,925 --> 01:10:00,896
WHEN ALL DREAMS CAME TRUE
IN MADELINE'S WAY.

1650
01:10:01,897 --> 01:10:04,800
[GIRLS GIGGLE]

1651
01:10:07,636 --> 01:10:10,339
THEN LORD CUCUFACE PROUDLY
STEPPED FORWARD TO SAY...

1652
01:10:10,372 --> 01:10:14,810
MESDAMES, MESSIEURS,
ET MES
 ENFANTS, IF I MAY,

1653
01:10:14,843 --> 01:10:18,414
I NOW DECLARE
THE NEW CITY SCHOOL
FOR GIRLS,

1654
01:10:18,447 --> 01:10:22,751
FUNDED SO GENEROUSLY
BY OUR VERY OWN MADELINE,

1655
01:10:22,785 --> 01:10:25,854
OFFICIALLY OPEN!

1656
01:10:25,888 --> 01:10:28,357
[APPLAUSE AND CHEERS]

1657
01:10:28,390 --> 01:10:29,825
AND MAY I SAY

1658
01:10:29,858 --> 01:10:34,330
THEY'RE ABSOLUTELY
TOP-DRAWER GIRLS,

1659
01:10:34,363 --> 01:10:36,699
THE VERY BEST.

1660
01:10:52,781 --> 01:10:54,717
POR USTED.

1661
01:10:57,453 --> 01:10:58,487
MERCI.

1662
01:10:58,520 --> 01:11:01,290
GRACIAS, PEPITO.

1663
01:11:02,524 --> 01:11:03,659
PERMISO.

1664
01:11:03,692 --> 01:11:04,727
FIFI!

1665
01:11:04,760 --> 01:11:05,561
[APPLAUDS]

1666
01:11:05,594 --> 01:11:08,597
MERCI
 BEAUCOUP,
 MADELINE.

1667
01:11:08,631 --> 01:11:10,799
I AM NOT COUGHING
AT LAST.

1668
01:11:10,833 --> 01:11:11,834
DR. COHN,

1669
01:11:11,867 --> 01:11:13,435
HE HAS
MADE ME BETTER.

1670
01:11:13,469 --> 01:11:16,538
FIFI IS
MY STAR PATIENT.

1671
01:11:16,572 --> 01:11:18,040
YOU WILL VISIT OFTEN?

1672
01:11:18,073 --> 01:11:19,108
OF COURSE.

1673
01:11:19,141 --> 01:11:20,276
WE ARE SISTER SCHOOLS.

1674
01:11:20,309 --> 01:11:24,813
I AM VERY IMPRESSED
YOU HAVE CHOSEN TO
DONATE YOUR REWARD

1675
01:11:24,847 --> 01:11:26,615
TO THE NEW SCHOOL,
MADELINE.

1676
01:11:26,649 --> 01:11:28,917
IT IS WHAT MAMA
WOULD HAVE WISHED--

1677
01:11:28,951 --> 01:11:30,986
TO SHARE WITH FAMILY.

1678
01:11:31,020 --> 01:11:32,621
I AM SO LUCKY

1679
01:11:32,655 --> 01:11:34,957
THAT MY FAMILY
IS SO VERY BIG.

1680
01:11:34,990 --> 01:11:39,995
AND SO IS
 YOUR HEART,
MA PETITE.

1681
01:11:44,900 --> 01:11:48,470
♪ ARMS TO WARM ME
WHEN I'M COLD ♪

1682
01:11:48,504 --> 01:11:51,073
♪ LIPS THAT SMILE
AND NEVER SCOLD ♪

1683
01:11:51,106 --> 01:11:54,810
♪ EARS THAT LISTEN,
 HANDS THAT HOLD ♪

1684
01:11:54,843 --> 01:11:58,380
♪ MY FRIENDS ARE
JUST LIKE FAMILY ♪

1685
01:11:58,414 --> 01:11:59,481
♪ FAMILY

1686
01:11:59,515 --> 01:12:01,784
♪ THE ONES WHO WIPE YOUR TEARS
WHEN YOU FEEL SMALL ♪

1687
01:12:01,817 --> 01:12:02,851
♪ FAMILY

1688
01:12:02,885 --> 01:12:05,421
♪ THE ONES WHO'LL ALWAYS
BE THERE WHEN YOU CALL ♪

1689
01:12:05,454 --> 01:12:06,388
♪ FAMILY

1690
01:12:06,422 --> 01:12:07,890
♪ THE ONES WHO TRULY
LOVE YOU MOST OF ALL ♪

1691
01:12:07,923 --> 01:12:11,126
Madeline: ♪ MY FRIENDS
ARE JUST LIKE FAMILY ♪

1692
01:12:11,160 --> 01:12:17,833
♪ OUR FRIENDS ARE
JUST LIKE FAMILY ♪

1693
01:12:17,866 --> 01:12:22,604
Narrator: MADELINE HAS
FRIENDS AND FAMILY GALORE,

1694
01:12:22,638 --> 01:12:23,972
AND THAT'S ALL THERE IS.

1695
01:12:24,006 --> 01:12:25,841
THERE ISN'T ANY MORE.

